		<item>
		<title>Bitcoin Poised for Further Gains After SoftBank Buy</title>
		<link>https://www.atfx.com/en-za/analysis/market-news/bitcoin-further-gains-softbank-buy</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ATFX]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 25 Apr 2025 03:01:06 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Market news & Insights]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Bitcoin - BTCUSD]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.atfx.com/?p=48542</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Japanese investment conglomerate SoftBank has announced another Bitcoin purchase plan despite losing on the token in 2018. BTCUSD – Daily Chart The price of BTCUSD has rallied this week to sit near $93,700 and a push to $100k Is possible next week.  Japanese investment giant SoftBank is testing the crypto waters again with the new [&#8230;]]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Japanese investment conglomerate SoftBank has announced another </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Bitcoin</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> purchase plan despite losing on the token in 2018.</span></p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-48544" src="https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/BTCUSD-–-Daily-Chart.png" alt="BTCUSD – Daily Chart" width="865" height="547" srcset="https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/BTCUSD-–-Daily-Chart.png 865w, https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/BTCUSD-–-Daily-Chart-300x190.png 300w, https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/BTCUSD-–-Daily-Chart-768x486.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 865px) 100vw, 865px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">BTCUSD – Daily Chart</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The price of </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">BTCUSD</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> has rallied this week to sit near $93,700 and a push to $100k Is possible next week. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Japanese investment giant SoftBank is testing the crypto waters again with the new bitcoin (BTC) investment vehicle, Twenty One Capital, in conjunction with Tether, Bitfinex, and Cantor Fitzgerald. It is another welcome sign of institutional flows for bulls. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">SoftBank Group has $308 billion assets under management and is another sign of a large corporation buying into the world’s largest <a href="https://www.atfx.com.bz/en-za/markets/cryptocurrencies" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cryptocurrency</a>. The US tech giant put a vote to its shareholders over the last year to invest in BTC but it was voted down. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">For other investors, there is a worry that it is a bad omen for crypto after a previous loss. In 2019, SoftBank made headlines when its founder, Masayoshi Son, took a big loss on a personal bitcoin investment. Son had taken exposure to cryptocurrency in late 2017, when the ICO mania was peaking and bitcoin was trading at an all-time high of around $20,000. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">With bitcoin now trading at $93,000, Son’s investment would have been very profitable had he held it. But he sold in early 2018 as bitcoin began to crash, resulting in a $130 million loss, according to the WSJ. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It remains to be seen how Son will do this time around but the move can help some short-term gains in Bitcoin after the coin has rallied from a recent correction. Some safe haven flows have arrived after ETF flows have been reduced. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The new TwentyOne investment vehicle has already placed $4bn of BTC on its balance sheet and looks set to add more in the coming months. A pause in tariffs could see less market volatility and a return to speculative investments.</span></p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
